2026-05-05 22:58:34,975 [INFO] autogen_core.events: {"type": "ToolCall", "tool_name": "board_write_file", "arguments": {"path": "separability_matrix_issue_description.md", "content": "## Issue: Incorrect separability matrix for nested CompoundModels\n\n### Description:\nThe `separability_matrix` function is not computing separability correctly for nested CompoundModels. For instance:\n\n```python\nfrom astropy.modeling import models as m\nfrom astropy.modeling.separable import separability_matrix\n\ncm = m.Linear1D(10) & m.Linear1D(5)\n```\n\nThe expected separability matrix:\n```python\n>>> separability_matrix(cm)\narray([[ True, False],\n       [False,  True]])\n```\n\nHowever, when nested:\n```python\n>>> separability_matrix(m.Pix2Sky_TAN() & cm)\narray([[ True,  True, False, False],\n       [ True,  True, False, False],\n       [False, False,  True,  True],\n       [False, False,  True,  True]])\n```\n\nThe expected separability seems incorrect as inputs and outputs are no longer separable.\n\n### Fail-to-pass tests:\n- astropy/modeling/tests/test_separable.py::test_separable[compound_model6-result6]\n- astropy/modeling/tests/test_separable.py::test_separable[compound_model9-result9]\n\n### Next Steps:\n1. Analyze the behavior of the `separability_matrix` function for nested CompoundModels.\n2. Identify the location of the bug in the code.\n3. Implement a fix to correct the computation.\n4. Update tests to validate the fix."}, "result": "Access denied - path outside allowed directories: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/separability_matrix_issue_description.md not in /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-evaluate-pipeline/runs/example-study/mas_centralize/astropy__astropy-12907/repeat_1/project_board", "agent_id": "ProjectManager_e6524bea-c0f6-4f60-b3b7-70b7550a5a2a/e6524bea-c0f6-4f60-b3b7-70b7550a5a2a"}
