2026-05-05 22:58:58,332 [INFO] autogen_core.events: {"type": "ToolCall", "tool_name": "board_write_file", "arguments": {"path": "nested_compound_model_bug_report.md", "content": "## Issue: Incorrect Separability Matrix in Nested CompoundModels\n\n### Issue Summary\n- `separability_matrix` returns unexpected results for nested CompoundModels, indicating incorrect separability between model components that should be independent.\n\n### Steps to Reproduce\n1. Import necessary components:\n   ```python\n   from astropy.modeling import models as m\n   from astropy.modeling.separable import separability_matrix\n   ```\n2. Define a simple compound model:\n   ```python\n   cm = m.Linear1D(10) & m.Linear1D(5)\n   ```\n3. Check the separability matrix:\n   ```python\n   expected_matrix = separability_matrix(cm)\n   print(expected_matrix)  # Should be: [[ True, False], [False,  True]]\n   ```\n4. Create a nested compound model:\n   ```python\n   nested = m.Pix2Sky_TAN() & cm\n   result_matrix = separability_matrix(nested)\n   print(result_matrix)  # Result is incorrect\n   ```\n\n### Expected Behavior\n- `separability_matrix` should correctly reflect separability for nested models. For the nested configuration, the expected result should maintain separability.\n\n### Current Failures\n- Failing tests include:  \n  - `test_separable[compound_model6-result6]`  \n  - `test_separable[compound_model9-result9]`\n\n### Recommended Actions\n1. Investigate the logic within `separability_matrix` for nested models.\n2. Revise the code as necessary to ensure accurate separability predictions.\n3. Enhance the test suite with additional cases if required."}, "result": "Access denied - path outside allowed directories: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/nested_compound_model_bug_report.md not in /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-evaluate-pipeline/runs/example-study/mas_centralize/astropy__astropy-12907/repeat_1/project_board", "agent_id": "ProjectManager_e6524bea-c0f6-4f60-b3b7-70b7550a5a2a/e6524b